The latest MSTest is **4.2.2** (major version jump from 3.x to 4.x). Here are the breaking changes relevant to **your project**:

---

### 🔴 `[ExpectedException]` is removed

This directly affects your two test methods. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`:

```csharp
// Before (v3)
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After (v4)
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

---

### Other v4 breaking changes (not hitting your code today, but worth knowing):

| Change | Impact |
|---|---|
| `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` → `ExecuteAsync` | Only if you have custom `TestMethodAttribute` subclasses |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Remove `ClassCleanupBehavior.EndOfClass` parameter from `[ClassCleanup]` |
| `Assert` APIs no longer accept `message` + `params object[]` | Use string interpolation instead |
| `TestContext.Properties` is now `IDictionary<string, object>` | `.Contains()` → `.ContainsKey()` |
| `TestTimeout` enum removed | Use `[Timeout(int.MaxValue)]` instead of `[Timeout(TestTimeout.Infinite)]` |
| `TestContext.ManagedType` removed | Use `FullyQualifiedTestClassName` |
| Minimum TFM is `net8.0` | You're already on net8.0 ✅ |

---

Want me to apply the fixes to your project (upgrade the package reference and migrate `[ExpectedException]` → `Assert.ThrowsExactly`)?
